The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Linen bash

 SAIONEE CHAKRABORTY

 Sabyasachi Mukherjee 

 at Linen Club; (top) chefs show off the Smorgasbord 

 spread at West View Bar amp; Grill. Pictures by Pabitra 

 Das and Rashbehari Das 

 What: 

 First anniversary celebrations of Club de Royale, an exclusive 

 Linen Club showroom.

 Where: 15, Loudon Street, beside Monapali.

 When: Wednesday afternoon.

 Take a look: For me, someone in linen has definitely got some class Its an acquired taste, smiled designer Sabyasachi Mukherjee, present to cut the birthday cake.

 The store is home to a brand new spring-summer range lots of embroidery, prints and hand-painted fabric. The colour palette is bright and sees lots of oranges, mauves and pinks. The ready-to-wear line comprises shirts, suits and jackets for men and women. There is unstitched fabric, too, with a set of three in-house designers helping you out with the cuts and patterns.

 We are going for an expansion. The 1,250-sq-ft showroom will be spread over 1,600 sq ft in the next two to three months. We will be housing a premium segment corner. Fifteen more Linen Club outlets spread across the country are in the pipeline, reveals Abhey Nair, senior vice-president, Jaya Shree Textiles that owns Linen Club.

 Grill fest

 What: The Gourmet Smorgasbord Grill promotion.

 Where: West View Bar and Grill, ITC Sonar Bangla Sheraton amp; Towers.

 When: From January 26 to February 4, for dinner only. 

 The spread: The assortment boasts of European culinary delights ranging from Australian Lamb Chops Marinated in Rosemary and Red Wine to Lime and Garlic Infused Norwegian Salmon Streaks to French Crepes Souzette. You can also dig into some Himalayan Trout, Baby Rock Lobster, Cold Smoked Loin of Pork or Tenderloin Mignonettes. 

 Vegetarians can opt for Fresh Tender Asparagus, Buffalo Mozzarella, Vine Ripened Zucchini Wraps and Wild Mushroom, and Pineapple Brochettes. 

 The cheese table offers an array of Cheddar, Edam, Swiss Emanthal, Danish Blue among a host of others. Potato lovers can sample Duchesse, Lyonnaise, Jacket and Walnut Mash with condiments or bite into Caponata of Chargrilled Mash and Candied Garlic.

 Pocket pinch: Non-vegetarian and vegetarian buffets are priced at Rs 1,750 and Rs 1,300.

 Voiceover: Smorgasbord 

 or smorg is a Scandinavian term for delectable array of 

 cold delicacies consisting of pork meats, pates, pies, terrines, 

 glantines and more. We have customised it to suit the Calcutta 

 palate, says Chef Ramesh Javvaji, executive chef, 

 ITC Sonar Bangla Sheraton amp; Towers. 




